### ULTRA-MINIMAL PROTOBUF ASSEMBLY CHECK
### Если этот запрос проходит, значит IntelliJ ломается не на сервисе, а на enum/map/audience в более сложных телах.
### Enum переданы числами:
### - priority: 2 = DELIVERY_PRIORITY_NORMAL
### - preferredChannel: 1 = CHANNEL_EMAIL
### - strategy.kind: 1 = STRATEGY_KIND_IMMEDIATE
GRPC localhost:9090/notification.facade.v1.NotificationFacade/CreateNotificationEvent
Content-Type: application/grpc
TE: trailers

{
  "idempotencyKey": "mail-proto-smoke-001",
  "templateId": "welcome-email",
  "templateVersion": 1,
  "priority": 2,
  "preferredChannel": 1,
  "strategy": {
    "kind": 1
  }
}

###
### Minimal gRPC flow for one mail event
### Run requests top-to-bottom and manually copy `event_id` / `dispatch_id` from responses if needed.

### 1) CreateNotificationEvent
GRPC localhost:9090/notification.facade.v1.NotificationFacade/CreateNotificationEvent
Content-Type: application/grpc
TE: trailers

{
  "idempotencyKey": "mail-single-event-001",
  "templateId": "welcome-email",
  "templateVersion": 1,
  "priority": "DELIVERY_PRIORITY_NORMAL",
  "preferredChannel": "CHANNEL_EMAIL",
  "strategy": {
    "kind": "STRATEGY_KIND_IMMEDIATE"
  },
  "payload": {
    "campaign": "single-event-check",
    "title": "Welcome",
    "body": "Single test event for facade"
  },
  "audience": {
    "kind": "AUDIENCE_KIND_EXPLICIT",
    "snapshotOnDispatch": true
  }
}

###
### 2) AddRecipients
### Insert the `eventId` from step 1 response manually.
GRPC localhost:9090/notification.facade.v1.NotificationFacade/AddRecipients
Content-Type: application/grpc
TE: trailers

{
  "eventId": "PUT_EVENT_ID_HERE",
  "idempotencyKey": "mail-single-add-001",
  "recipientId": [
    "mail-user-1001",
    "mail-user-1002"
  ]
}

###
### 3) TriggerDispatch
### Insert the same `eventId` from step 1 response manually.
GRPC localhost:9090/notification.facade.v1.NotificationFacade/TriggerDispatch
Content-Type: application/grpc
TE: trailers

{
  "eventId": "PUT_EVENT_ID_HERE",
  "idempotencyKey": "mail-single-dispatch-001"
}
